Probabiility Functions

R Paradigm for Probability Distributions

Some of the key distributions: >- binomial >- Poisson >- hypergeometric >- exponential >- normal >- \(\chi^2\) >- Student t

R Paradigm for Probability Distributions

  • Family of functions; members identified by prefix
  • 4 common prefixes
    • __d*__ - density (or mass) function
    • __p*__ - cumulative probability function
    • __q*__ - inverse probability i.e.quantile
    • __r*__ - random value generators

Example: Binomial Distribution
